    {
      "id": "github-howto-step-status",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Status Strip",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Read the status strip first\n\nThe toolbar is the authoritative summary surface.\n\n- **Document** tells you what graph you are actually on.\n- **Save target** tells you where the next save is pointed.\n- **Access** tells you which GitHub installation context Twilite is using.\n\nWhen `Document` and `Save target` disagree, treat that as the first thing to resolve before writing."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-howto-step-save",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Save Flow",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 400
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Save a graph to GitHub\n\n1. Open **Save to GitHub** from the toolbar.\n2. Choose the **Installation** that can see the destination repo.\n3. Choose the **Repository**.\n4. Confirm **Branch** and **File path in repo**.\n5. Read the capability pill next to the save button.\n\nInterpret the capability pill like this:\n- **Writable**: Twilite has high confidence a direct commit should work.\n- **Accessible**: GitHub can reach the destination, but Twilite cannot fully predict the final write outcome.\n- **Blocked**: the selected installation cannot access that repo directly."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-howto-step-repos",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Missing Repos",
      "position": {
        "x": 340,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 640,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## If a repo is missing\n\nMissing repos are usually an installation-scope issue, not a local-folder issue.\n\n- Local folders do **not** make a repo visible to Twilite.\n- Workspace mappings are defaults, not GitHub authority.\n- The repo picker only shows repos returned by the selected GitHub App installation.\n\nSo if you expect `owner/public` or `owner/private` and do not see it, inspect the GitHub App installation settings first."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-howto-step-model",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Mental Model",
      "position": {
        "x": 340,
        "y": 440
      },
      "width": 640,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Current mental model\n\nTwilite's current GitHub integration is built around four separate ideas:\n\n- **Document identity**: the `github://...` graph you opened.\n- **Save target**: the repo, branch, and path the next write will use.\n- **Installation access**: what the selected GitHub App installation can actually see.\n- **Workspace mapping**: your preferred `work`, `public`, or `private` default.\n\nThe UI is safest when it keeps those separate. The how-to is about operating that model cleanly, not pretending they are all the same thing."
      }
    },
